# Implementation Plan: Enhance E-Library Content

Enhance the content of e-library materials (Curriculum, Notes, etc.) to look and feel professional, structured, and information-dense, moving away from the current "pamphlet-like" appearance.

## Proposed Changes

### [Library Expansion] Bulk Module Seeding

#### [NEW] seed_all_modules.ts
A new script to handle the creation of over 100 modules across all programs.
- **Section A (Foundation)**: Will be marked as `is_common: true` and categorized under "Foundation Modules".
- **Sections B-P (Program Specific)**: Will be linked to their respective [Program](file:///media/swastik/focus/ldm%20feb/src/app/%28student%29/student/library/page.tsx#31-36) via `course_code` and categorized under "Module Notes".
- **Section Q (Certificates)**: Specifically for Ayurvedic certificate programs.
- **Content Strategy**: 
    - Use a structured "Cheat Notes" template for all modules.
    - Template includes: "Concept Map", "High-Yield Facts", "Exam Highlights", and "Quick Recall".
    - Populate sample content for major modules and structured placeholders for others.

### [Content Quality] Academic Upgrade (Phase 3)
To address concerns about content depth and tone, we are upgrading the library modules from "Cheat Notes" to full "Academic Books".

#### [REGENERATE] 100+ Module Books
- **Professional Tone**: Shift from "quick summary" to "scholarly and pedagogical".
- **Multi-Chapter Structure**: Instead of a single outline, each book will have 5-8 detailed chapters.
- **Pedagogical Elements**: Include "Clinical Case Studies", "Pharmacological Summaries", "Safety Protocols", and "Academic Vocabulary".
- **Content Expansion**: Each module will have 3000+ words of structured text instead of 500.

### [Library UI] Program-Based Navigation

#### [MODIFY] /api/public/library/route.ts
- Populate `course_id` (Program) for each document.
- Include `program_code` and `program_name` in the response.

#### [NEW] /api/public/programs/route.ts
- Create a new public endpoint to fetch all available programs (code and name).

#### [MODIFY] /app/(public)/library/page.tsx
- Update sidebar to include a "Programs" navigation section.
- Implement logic to filter documents specifically by selected Program.
- Add "Common Foundation" as a primary category.

#### [MODIFY] /app/(student)/student/library/page.tsx
- Apply similar program-based navigation for the student portal.

### [Admin Experience] File CRUD & UI Fixes (Phase 4)
To provide full management capabilities, we will implement direct file uploads and fix structural UI bugs in the admin portal.

#### [NEW] /api/admin/library/upload/route.ts
- Create a new endpoint to handle `multipart/form-data`.
- Save files to `public/uploads/library` and return the relative path.

#### [MODIFY] CategoryManager.tsx & DocumentUploadModal.tsx
- **Fix "Invalid Date" bug**: Provide fallbacks for `createdAt` in tables.
- **Implement File Upload**: Add a "Choose File" input that triggers the new upload API.
- **Enhanced CRUD**: Ensure Edit and Version History work seamlessly with uploaded files.
- **Markdown Support**: Enable `.md` as a primary format type for AI-driven academic content.

### [User Experience] Premium Reader Interface (Phase 5)
To create a "wow" factor, we will replace the basic modal with a high-end medical book reader designed in Stitch.

#### [NEW] Premium Book Reader Component
- **Format Support Strategy**:
    - **Academic Books (Rich-Text & Markdown)**: Rendered in a high-end, custom-styled "Study Interface" with Chapter navigation and professional medical typography. Markdown support allows for beautiful display of AI-generated content.
    - **PDF Documents**: Embedded directly in the reader using a high-quality frame, allowing students/visitors to read without leaving the app.
    - **Office Docs (Word, Excel)**: Handled via specialized "Resource Cards" with download links and format-specific icons.
- **Full Portal Integration**:
    - **Student Portal**: Integrated into `/(student)/student/library/page.tsx`.
    - **Public Portal**: Integrated into `/(public)/library/page.tsx` for open access.
- **Academic Features**:
    - **Chapter Navigation**: Left sidebar for jumping between sections in rich-text books.
    - **High-Yield Sidebars**: Gutter areas for summarizing key medical facts and pharmacology constants.
    - **Reader Settings**: Options for font size and "Night Mode" readability.

